@meetmangukiya unfortunately graph doesn't work in reverse, but both of these are pretty cool. You run both in the freecodecamp directory locally:
`git log --oneline --abbrev-commit --graph` (graph from most recent commit; page down with spacebar)
`git log --pretty=oneline --reverse --decorate --all` (commit list from original commit; page down with spacebar)

